The Motoko backend uses the Thebes backend library (`thebes-lib`) and the
Motoko `core` package. The design is informed by public ISO 20022 message
catalogues and by Thebes example canister patterns.

`motoko/InPlaceSha256d.mo` is vendored from the Menese LiteCoin-node
allocation-free Merkle/SHA-256d contribution:
https://github.com/Menese-Protocol/LiteCoin-node/pull/1
